4. What did we achieve?
With useEffect:

Browser fetches data

UI shows after fetch

SEO not good

Slower

Needs client JS

With Suspense:

Server fetches data (fast)

Suspense streams to client

SEO perfect

Faster

Less client JS

No need for useEffect

ğŸŸ¡ 5. When Suspense CANNOT replace useEffect

You still need useEffect for:

âœ” Button clicks â†’ fetch
âœ” User searches
âœ” Filters
âœ” Infinite scroll
âœ” Client-only APIs
âœ” localStorage, cookies
âœ” Live update (polling)

Suspense cannot handle these.

â­ Final Answer

â¡ï¸ Suspense can replace useEffect only when the data comes from the server.
â¡ï¸ If the fetch depends on user interaction or runs in the browser â†’ useEffect is required.

************************************************************************************************************88
When to use which
Scenario	Recommended approach
Server already fetches data, you just want to render it in Client Component	use hook + <Suspense>
You want to fetch data entirely on the client (after page load, on user action)	useEffect + useState
Need complex client-side caching, revalidation, or infinite scroll	SWR or React Query